  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Season the chicken pieces with salt, black pepper, cumin, and paprika.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Sear the chicken pieces until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Remove the chicken from the pot and set aside.",
    "Add the chopped onion to the pot and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional minute.",
    "Add the pitted dates, chicken broth, honey, and apricot jam to the pot.",
    "Stir to combine and bring the mixture to a simmer.",
    "Return the chicken to the pot and transfer to the preheated oven.",
    "Roast the chicken for 25-30 minutes, or until cooked through.",
    "Garnish with chopped cilantro and sprinkle with shichimi togarashi before serving."
  ],
